[{"location":"usage/#RefractiveIndexDatabase.jl","page":"Usage","title":"RefractiveIndexDatabase.jl","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"usage/","page":"Usage","title":"Usage","text":"Modules = [RefractiveIndexDatabase]\nPages = [\"RefractiveIndexDatabase.jl\", \"database.jl\"]","category":"page"},{"location":"usage/#RefractiveIndexDatabase.get_material-Tuple{Any, Any, Any}","page":"Usage","title":"RefractiveIndexDatabase.get_material","text":"get_material(shelf, book, page)\n\nLoad the refractive index data for the material corresponding to the specified shelf, book, and page within the refractiveindex.info database. The data can be queried by calling the returned object at a given wavelength.\n\nExamples\n\njulia> using RefractiveIndexDatabase\n\njulia> MgLiTaO3 = get_material(\"other\", \"Mg-LiTaO3\", \"Moutzouris-o\")\n\"Mg-LiTaO3 (Moutzouris et al. 2011: n(o) 0.450-1.551 µm; 8 mol.% Mg)\"\n\njulia> MgLiTaO3(0.45) # default unit is microns\n2.2373000025056826\n\njulia> using Unitful\n\njulia> MgLiTaO3(450u\"nm\") # auto-conversion from generic Unitful.jl length units\n2.2373000025056826\n\njulia> MgLiTaO3(450e-9, \"m\") # strings can be used to specify units (parsing is cached)\n2.2373000025056826\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"usage/#RefractiveIndexDatabase.info-Tuple","page":"Usage","title":"RefractiveIndexDatabase.info","text":"info(key)\n\nReturn with the metadata for the material corresponding to the given key.\n\njulia> info(\"main\", \"Ag\", \"Johnson\")\nRefractiveIndexDatabase.MaterialEntry\n  name: Johnson and Christy 1972: n,k 0.188-1.94 µm\n  book_category: Ag - Silver\n  page_category: Experimental data: bulk, thick film\n  path: main/Ag/Johnson.yml\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"usage/#RefractiveIndexDatabase.load_file-Tuple{Any}","page":"Usage","title":"RefractiveIndexDatabase.load_file","text":"load_file(path)\n\nLoad the refractive index data for the material corresponding to a YAML file within the refractiveindex.info database. The data can be queried by calling the returned object at a given wavelength.\n\nExamples\n\njulia> using RefractiveIndexDatabase\n\njulia> path = joinpath(RefractiveIndexDatabase.DB_ROOT, \"data\", \"main\", \"Ar\", \"Peck-15C.yml\");\n\njulia> Ar = load_file(path)\nRefractiveIndexDatabase.FormulaN\n\njulia> Ar(532, \"nm\")\n1.0002679711455778\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"usage/#RefractiveIndexDatabase.load_url-Tuple{Any}","page":"Usage","title":"RefractiveIndexDatabase.load_url","text":"load_url(path)\n\nLoad the refractive index data for the material corresponding to the specified url within the refractiveindex.info database. The data can be queried by calling the returned object at a given wavelength.\n\nExamples\n\njulia> using RefractiveIndexDatabase\n\njulia> Ar = load_url(\"https://refractiveindex.info/database/data/main/Ar/Peck-15C.yml\")\nRefractiveIndexDatabase.FormulaN\n\njulia> Ar(532, \"nm\")\n1.0002679711455778\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"usage/#RefractiveIndexDatabase.search-Tuple{}","page":"Usage","title":"RefractiveIndexDatabase.search","text":"search(shelf=\"\", book=\"\", page=\"\")\n\nReturns with a set of keys for all materials in the database that match the given query.\n\njulia> RefractiveIndexDatabase.search()\nSet{Tuple{String, String, String}} with 2915 elements:\n  (\"glass\", \"HIKARI-F\", \"F1\")\n  (\"main\", \"Au\", \"Ciesielski\")\n  (\"glass\", \"SUMITA-PG\", \"K-PG375\")\n  (\"glass\", \"SUMITA-VC\", \"K-VC179\")\n  (\"glass\", \"SUMITA-SFLD\", \"K-SFLD11\")\n  (\"main\", \"SrF2\", \"Li\")\n  (\"glass\", \"SCHOTT-SK\", \"N-SK11\")\n  (\"main\", \"BaB2O4\", \"Zhang-o\")\n  (\"glass\", \"OHARA-BAH\", \"BAH54\")\n  (\"glass\", \"HIKARI-LaSF\", \"E-LASFH9\")\n  (\"main\", \"ZnTe\", \"Marple\")\n  (\"main\", \"Si\", \"Green-2008\")\n  (\"glass\", \"HOYA-TaF\", \"M-TAF31\")\n  (\"main\", \"C\", \"Djurisic-e\")\n  (\"organic\", \"propanol\", \"Sani\")\n  (\"glass\", \"BARBERINI-sun-protection\", \"D6420\")\n  (\"3d\", \"crystals\", \"germanium\")\n  (\"glass\", \"SCHOTT-SK\", \"P-SK60\")\n  (\"glass\", \"SUMITA-GIR\", \"K-GIR79\")\n  (\"glass\", \"SCHOTT-F\", \"F2HT\")\n  (\"glass\", \"OHARA-LAM\", \"LAM59\")\n  (\"main\", \"He\", \"Borzsonyi\")\n  ⋮\n\njulia> RefractiveIndexDatabase.search(book=\"Ag\", shelf=\"main\")\nSet{Tuple{String, String, String}} with 31 elements:\n  (\"main\", \"AgGaSe2\", \"Harasaki-o\")\n  (\"main\", \"Ag\", \"Johnson\")\n  (\"main\", \"Ag\", \"Rakic-BB\")\n  (\"main\", \"AgCl\", \"Tilton\")\n  (\"main\", \"Ag\", \"Jiang\")\n  (\"main\", \"Ag\", \"Choi\")\n  (\"main\", \"AgGaS2\", \"Boyd-o\")\n  (\"main\", \"Ag3AsS3\", \"Hulme-e\")\n  (\"main\", \"AgGaS2\", \"Kato-e\")\n  (\"main\", \"AgGaS2\", \"Kato-o\")\n  (\"main\", \"Ag\", \"Ciesielski-Ge\")\n  (\"main\", \"Ag\", \"McPeak\")\n  (\"main\", \"AgGaSe2\", \"Boyd-e\")\n  (\"main\", \"Ag\", \"Ciesielski-Ni\")\n  (\"main\", \"Ag\", \"Werner\")\n  (\"main\", \"AgGaS2\", \"Boyd-e\")\n  (\"main\", \"AgBr\", \"Schröter\")\n  (\"main\", \"AgGaS2\", \"Takaoka-e\")\n  (\"main\", \"Ag\", \"Werner-DFT\")\n  (\"main\", \"Ag\", \"Yang\")\n  (\"main\", \"Ag\", \"Stahrenberg\")\n  (\"main\", \"Ag\", \"Windt\")\n  ⋮\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"formulas/","page":"Formualas","title":"Formualas","text":"Modules = [RefractiveIndexDatabase]\nPages   = [\"formulas.jl\"]","category":"page"},{"location":"formulas/#RefractiveIndexDatabase.Cauchy","page":"Formualas","title":"RefractiveIndexDatabase.Cauchy","text":"Cauchy formula:\n\nn = c_1 + sum limits_i=5^N c_2i lambda^c_2i+1\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"formulas/#RefractiveIndexDatabase.Exotic","page":"Formualas","title":"RefractiveIndexDatabase.Exotic","text":"Exotic formula:\n\nn^2 = c_1\n    + fracc_2lambda^2 - c_3\n    + fracc_4(lambda - c_5)(lambda - c_5)^2 + c_6\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"formulas/#RefractiveIndexDatabase.Gases","page":"Formualas","title":"RefractiveIndexDatabase.Gases","text":"Gases formula:\n\nn - 1 = c_1\n    + sum limits_i=1^N fracc_2ic_2i+1 - lambda^-2 \n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"formulas/#RefractiveIndexDatabase.Herzberger","page":"Formualas","title":"RefractiveIndexDatabase.Herzberger","text":"Herzberger formula:\n\nn = c_1\n    + fracc_2lambda^2 - 0028\n    + c_3 left( frac1lambda^2 - 0028 right)^2\n    + sum limits_i=1^N c_i+3 lambda^2i\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"formulas/#RefractiveIndexDatabase.Polynomial","page":"Formualas","title":"RefractiveIndexDatabase.Polynomial","text":"Polynomial formula:\n\nn^2 = c_1 + sum limits_i=1^N  c_2i lambda^c_2i+1\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"formulas/#RefractiveIndexDatabase.RIInfo","page":"Formualas","title":"RefractiveIndexDatabase.RIInfo","text":"RefractiveIndex.INFO formula:\n\nn^2 = c_1\n    + fracc_2 lambda^c_3lambda^2 - c_4^c_5\n    + fracc_6 lambda^c_7lambda^2 - c_8^c_9\n    + sum limits_i=5^N c_2i lambda^c_2i+1\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"formulas/#RefractiveIndexDatabase.Retro","page":"Formualas","title":"RefractiveIndexDatabase.Retro","text":"Retro formula:\n\nfracn^2 - 1n^2 +2 = c_1\n    + fracc_2 lambda^2lambda^2 - c_3\n    +  c_4 lambda^2\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"formulas/#RefractiveIndexDatabase.Sellmeier","page":"Formualas","title":"RefractiveIndexDatabase.Sellmeier","text":"Sellmeier formula:\n\nn^2 - 1 = c_1 + sum limits_i=1^N fracc_2i lambda^2lambda^2 - c_2i+1^2\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"formulas/#RefractiveIndexDatabase.Sellmeier2","page":"Formualas","title":"RefractiveIndexDatabase.Sellmeier2","text":"Sellmeier-2 formula:\n\nn^2 - 1 = c_1 + sum limits_i=1^N fracc_2i lambda^2lambda^2 - c_2i+1\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"#RefractiveIndexDatabase","page":"Home","title":"RefractiveIndexDatabase","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Provides an offline/online interface to refractiveindex.info.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"This package is based on https://github.com/stillyslalom/RefractiveIndex.jl repository.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"The source of the database: https://github.com/polyanskiy/refractiveindex.info-database","category":"page"},{"location":"#Examples","page":"Home","title":"Examples","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"julia> using RefractiveIndexDatabase\n\njulia> MgLiTaO3 = get_material(\"other\", \"Mg-LiTaO3\", \"Moutzouris-o\")\nRefractiveIndexDatabase.RealFormula\n\njulia> MgLiTaO3(0.45) # default unit is microns\n2.2373000025056826\n\njulia> using Unitful\n\njulia> MgLiTaO3(450u\"nm\") # auto-conversion from generic Unitful.jl length units\n2.2373000025056826\n\njulia> MgLiTaO3(450e-9, \"m\") # strings can be used to specify units (parsing is cached)\n2.2373000025056826\n\njulia> Ar = load_url(\"https://refractiveindex.info/database/data/main/Ar/Peck-15C.yml\")\nRefractiveIndexDatabase.RealFormula\n\njulia> Ar(532, \"nm\")\n1.0002679711455778","category":"page"},{"location":"#Index","page":"Home","title":"Index","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"","category":"page"}]
